# Testing Requirements

**Automatic test generation:** When creating or modifying source files under `src/`, always create or update the corresponding colocated test file(s) **without waiting for the user to ask**. Use the test-generation skill (`agent-os/skills/test-generation/SKILL.md`) for templates. The code-structure skill (`agent-os/skills/code-structure/SKILL.md`) also requires tests to be added as part of any requirement implementation.

When a NEW `.ts` or `.tsx` file is created under `src/`, automatically check if a colocated test file exists. If not, create one using the test-generation skill.

## Rules

1. Every component (`*.tsx`) in `src/shared/components/`, `src/shared/forms/`, `src/shared/layouts/` MUST have a colocated `*.test.tsx` file
2. Every component/hook/form under **`src/pages/**` route islands** MUST ship a colocated `*.test.ts(x)` **beside its source** (folder-per-unit: `components/<X>/<X>.tsx` + `<X>.test.tsx`). The island's top-level `<Page>Page.tsx`/`<Page>Layout.tsx` ships `<Page>Page.test.tsx` next to it.
3. Every service/utility (`*.ts`) in `src/core/`, `src/lib/`, `src/stores/` MUST have a colocated `*.test.ts` file
4. Every TanStack Query hook MUST ship a colocated `*.test.ts` beside its source (`hooks/use<X>/use<X>.test.ts`) — in both shared and page islands
5. Component tests MUST include `vitest-axe` accessibility assertions (`toHaveNoViolations()`)
6. **Colocated beside source everywhere** — `shared/`, `core/`, `lib/`, `stores/`, AND `pages/` islands. Cross-component *integration* flows for a page may additionally live in `pages/<page>/__tests__/integration/`
7. All components MUST have `data-testid` attributes following the naming convention below
8. Coverage thresholds: 80% branches, functions, lines, statements (enforced in `vitest.config.ts`)
9. Vitest runs colocated `src/**/*.test.{ts,tsx}` (plus `src/**/__tests__/**`); it **excludes** `tests/e2e` (Playwright owns those)

## data-testid Convention

| Element        | Pattern          | Example                        |
| -------------- | ---------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Page container | `<name>-page`    | `data-testid="dashboard-page"` |
| Form           | `<name>-form`    | `data-testid="login-form"`     |
| Form input     | `<form>-<field>` | `data-testid="login-email"`    |
| Submit button  | `<form>-submit`  | `data-testid="login-submit"`   |
| Error message  | `form-error`     | `data-testid="form-error"`     |

## Naming Convention

Colocated beside source **everywhere** (shared/core/lib/stores AND pages islands):

| Source File         | Colocated test (same folder)   |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `Button.tsx`        | `Button.test.tsx`              |
| `useMeContext.ts`   | `useMeContext.test.ts`         |
| `DashboardPage.tsx` | `DashboardPage.test.tsx`       |

## E2E & integration tests (`tests/e2e/`)

Playwright specs follow core-be's `<name>.<kind>.test.ts` (the backend uses
`.unit.`/`.integration.`/`.contract.`/`.e2e.`):

- **`<name>.e2e.test.ts`** — full-stack UI flow against the mock backend.
- **`<name>.integration.test.ts`** — contract against the running core-be (:3000);
  self-contained (inline signup/server-up/bearer helpers, no shared util), and
  auto-skips when the server is unreachable. The UI-through-to-backend spec
  (`app.integration.test.ts`) is gated behind `E2E_INTEGRATION=1` + `VITE_USE_MOCK_API=false`.

`playwright.config.ts` matches `/\.(e2e|integration)\.test\.ts$/`; Vitest excludes
`tests/e2e`. **Never** use `.spec.ts`, or the words "real"/"live", in test file names.

## Exceptions (no test required)

- Type definition files (`types.ts`, `contracts.ts`)
- Re-export barrel files (`index.ts`)
- Route marker files (`<page>.route.tsx`, `<page>.manifest.ts`)
- Configuration files (`constants.ts`)
- CSS files
- Branded type definition files (e.g., `branded.ts`)

## Test Infrastructure

| Tool                        | Purpose                                              |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Vitest                      | Unit test runner (globals enabled)                   |
| React Testing Library       | Component rendering + queries                        |
| vitest-axe                  | Accessibility assertions (auto-extended in setup)    |
| @testing-library/user-event | Realistic user interactions                          |
| @axe-core/playwright        | E2E accessibility scanning                           |
| Playwright                  | E2E browser tests (Chromium — the single maintained project) |
| Stryker                     | Mutation testing (CI-only, weekly)                   |

## Auto-Trigger (No User Input Required)

- When creating a **new** source file under `src/`, **immediately** generate the corresponding test file using the test-generation skill (`agent-os/skills/test-generation/SKILL.md`). Do not ask the user whether to add tests.
- When implementing any requirement (new page, component, hook, service), add or update tests as part of the same change set. See `agent-os/skills/code-structure/SKILL.md` for the full implementation checklist.
- Tests are mandatory for all non-exception files; generating them is part of the implementation, not an optional follow-up.
- **Strict colocation is validator-enforced** (`pnpm validate:structure`): every unit folder (`components/`, `forms/`, `hooks/`, `dialogs/`, `store/` — in pages, family-shared, and root shared), every island's top-level `<Page>Page/Layout.tsx`, and every flat-group component file MUST contain/ship a colocated `*.test.*`, or validation fails. Exemptions: route/manifest/contracts/search/fixtures/constants role files, barrels, OVERVIEW docs.
